        "    # Use recursive glob pattern to find all images\n",
        "    IMAGE_PATH_LIST = list(IMAGE_PATH.rglob(\"**/*.jpg\")) + list(IMAGE_PATH.rglob(\"**/*.JPG\")) + \\\n",
        "                      list(IMAGE_PATH.rglob(\"**/*.jpeg\")) + list(IMAGE_PATH.rglob(\"**/*.JPEG\"))\n",

        "    img2 = list(img.glob(\"*.jpg\"))\n",
        "    img_selected = random.choices(img2, k = 3)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i,image_selected in enumerate(img_selected):\n",
        "\n",
        "        img = cv2.imread(str(image_selected))\n",
        "        img = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",

        "        ax[p,i].set_title(f'Class: {c}\\nshape: {img.shape}')\n",
        "        ax[p,i].axis('off')\n",
        "\n",
        "    p+=1\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.tight_layout()\n",
        "fig.show()"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "The above images from the both set Training and Test set have different heights and widths. Let's better visualize how the width and height of images are distributed in both datasets."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "gohsCzsT5xvV"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "CuSCbzSRCgc6"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "IMAGE_PATH_TRAIN = Path(\"/content/drive/My Drive/Colab Notebooks/dataset/train\")\n",
        "\n",
        "IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_jpg = list(IMAGE_PATH_TRAIN.glob(\"*/*.jpg\"))\n",
        "IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_JPG = list(IMAGE_PATH_TRAIN.glob(\"*/*.JPG\"))\n",
        "IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_jpeg = list(IMAGE_PATH_TRAIN.glob(\"*/*.jpeg\"))\n",
        "\n",
        "IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_TOTAL = IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_jpg + IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_JPG\\\n",
        "                        + IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_jpeg\n",
        "\n",
        "seq_height = [None] * len(IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_TOTAL)\n",
        "seq_width = [None] * len(IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_TOTAL)\n",
        "\n",
        "for i,j in enumerate(IMAGE_PATH_LIST_TRAIN_TOTAL):\n",
        "    img_bgr = cv2.imread(str((j)))\n",
        "    img_rgb = cv2.cvtColor(img_bgr, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB)\n",
        "    seq_height[i] = img_rgb.shape[0]\n",
        "    seq_width[i] = img_rgb.shape[1]"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 416
        },
        "id": "GWYE47H6C1Xs",
        "outputId": "cb20efc1-ab0c-4d42-a0a6-9d934eb2383a"

          "output_type": "display_data",

              "<Figure size 1000x410 with 2 Axes>"
            ],
            "image/png": "\n"
          },
          "metadata": {}
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "fig,ax = plt.subplots(nrows = 1, ncols = 2, figsize = (10,4.1))\n",
        "sns.set_style('darkgrid')\n",
        "ax = ax.flat\n",
        "\n",
        "sns.histplot(seq_height, kde = True, line_kws = {'linewidth':2.3}, color = 'purple', ax = ax[0])\n",
        "ax[0].set_title('Distribution of Height')\n",
        "sns.histplot(seq_width, kde = True, line_kws = {'linewidth':2.3}, color = 'gray', ax = ax[1])\n",
        "ax[1].set_title('Distribution of Width')\n",
        "\n",
        "fig.tight_layout()\n",
        "fig.show()"
      ]

              "    <script>\n",
              "      const buttonEl =\n",
              "        document.querySelector('#df-5b15e115-4ed9-46aa-9483-5d0db2d4bfbd button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-5b15e115-4ed9-46aa-9483-5d0db2d4bfbd');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",

              "        document.querySelector('#df-3af27fc9-fdb8-4b4f-b908-313db80aa36b button.colab-df-convert');\n",
              "      buttonEl.style.display =\n",
              "        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';\n",
              "\n",
              "      async function convertToInteractive(key) {\n",
              "        const element = document.querySelector('#df-3af27fc9-fdb8-4b4f-b908-313db80aa36b');\n",
              "        const dataTable =\n",
              "          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',\n",
              "                                                    [key], {});\n",
              "        if (!dataTable) return;\n",
              "\n",
              "        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +\n",
              "          '<a target=\"_blank\" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'\n",
              "          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';\n",
              "        element.innerHTML = '';\n",
              "        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';\n",
              "        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);\n",
              "        const docLink = document.createElement('div');\n",
              "        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;\n",
              "        element.appendChild(docLink);\n",
              "      }\n",
              "    </script>\n",
              "  </div>\n",
              "\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Creating custom dataset"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tGKqZG-b8kaj"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "XjxBA0myDmhu"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "class CustomDataset(Dataset):\n",
        "    def __init__(self, dataframe:pd.DataFrame, transform):\n",
        "        self.dataframe = dataframe\n",
        "        self.transform = transform\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __len__(self):\n",
        "        return len(self.dataframe)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def __getitem__(self, idx):\n",
        "        image_path = self.dataframe.iloc[idx,0]\n",
        "        image = Image.open(image_path).convert('RGB')\n",
        "        image = self.transform(image)\n",
        "        label = self.dataframe.iloc[idx,1]\n",
        "        return image,label"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vZ2jU0UYDovg"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "train_dataset = CustomDataset(df_train_path_label, auto_transforms)\n",
        "\n",
        "test_dataset = CustomDataset(df_test_path_label, auto_transforms)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Creating custom DataLoaders"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "JZzslMlA8qSW"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Guz-21LKDr0a"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "BATCH_SIZE = 4\n",
        "NUM_WORKERS = os.cpu_count()\n",
        "\n",
        "train_dataloader = DataLoader(dataset = train_dataset,\n",
        "                              batch_size = BATCH_SIZE,\n",
        "                              shuffle = True,\n",
        "                              num_workers = NUM_WORKERS)\n",
        "\n",
        "test_dataloader = DataLoader(dataset = test_dataset,\n",
        "                              batch_size = BATCH_SIZE,\n",
        "                              shuffle = False,\n",
        "                              num_workers = NUM_WORKERS)"
      ]
    },

        "#Defing the loss function and the optimizer\n",
        "loss_fn = nn.CrossEntropyLoss()\n",
        "optimizer = optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr = 0.01)"

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "Now defining 3 function to execute the traaning\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "*   train_step\n",
        "*   test_step\n",
        "*   train\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "DnkGMpic_P8a"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ffavNSohEV2q"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def train_step(model:torch.nn.Module,\n",
        "               dataloader:torch.utils.data.DataLoader,\n",
        "               loss_fn:torch.nn.Module,\n",
        "               optimizer:torch.optim.Optimizer):\n",
        "\n",
        "    model.train()\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_loss = 0.\n",
        "    accuracy_train = MulticlassAccuracy(num_classes = len(classes)).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for batch,(X,y) in enumerate(dataloader):\n",
        "        X,y = X.to(device), y.to(device)\n",
        "        optimizer.zero_grad()\n",
        "        y_pred_logit = model(X)\n",
        "        loss = loss_fn(y_pred_logit, y)\n",
        "        train_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "\n",
        "        loss.backward()\n",
        "        optimizer.step()\n",
        "\n",
        "        y_pred_prob = torch.softmax(y_pred_logit, dim = 1)\n",
        "        y_pred_class = torch.argmax(y_pred_prob, dim = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "        accuracy_train.update(y_pred_class, y)\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_loss = train_loss/len(dataloader)\n",
        "    train_accuracy = accuracy_train.compute()\n",
        "    accuracy_train.reset()\n",
        "\n",
        "    return train_loss, train_accuracy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "R6h6D5RcEYPY"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def save_checkpoint(filename, model, epoch, loss, optimizer, metric):\n",
        "    state = {\"filename\":filename,\n",
        "             \"model\":model.state_dict(),\n",
        "             \"epoch\":epoch,\n",
        "             \"loss\":loss,\n",
        "             \"optimizer\":optimizer.state_dict(),\n",
        "             \"metric\":metric}\n",
        "\n",
        "    torch.save(state, filename)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SQxe5htuEauT"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def test_step(model:torch.nn.Module,\n",
        "              dataloader:torch.utils.data.DataLoader,\n",
        "              loss_fn:torch.nn.Module):\n",
        "\n",
        "    model.eval()\n",
        "\n",
        "    test_loss = 0.\n",
        "    accuracy_test = MulticlassAccuracy(num_classes = len(classes)).to(device)\n",
        "\n",
        "    with torch.inference_mode():\n",
        "\n",
        "        for batch,(X,y) in enumerate(dataloader):\n",
        "            X,y = X.to(device), y.to(device)\n",
        "            y_pred_logit = model(X)\n",
        "            loss = loss_fn(y_pred_logit, y)\n",
        "            test_loss += loss.item()\n",
        "\n",
        "            y_pred_prob = torch.softmax(y_pred_logit, dim = 1)\n",
        "            y_pred_class = torch.argmax(y_pred_prob, dim = 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "            accuracy_test.update(y_pred_class, y)\n",
        "\n",
        "    test_loss = test_loss/len(dataloader)\n",
        "    test_accuracy = accuracy_test.compute()\n",
        "    accuracy_test.reset()\n",
        "\n",
        "    return test_loss, test_accuracy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "phEGZM5sEgWo"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "def train(model:torch.nn.Module,\n",
        "          train_dataloader:torch.utils.data.DataLoader,\n",
        "          test_dataloader:torch.utils.data.DataLoader,\n",
        "          loss_fn:torch.nn.Module,\n",
        "          optimizer:torch.optim.Optimizer,\n",
        "          epochs:int):\n",
        "\n",
        "    results = {\"train_loss\":[],\n",
        "               \"train_accuracy\":[],\n",
        "               \"test_loss\":[],\n",
        "               \"test_accuracy\":[]}\n",
        "\n",
        "    best_test_loss = float(\"inf\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    for epoch in tqdm(range(epochs)):\n",
        "\n",
        "        train_loss, train_accuracy = train_step(model = model,\n",
        "                                                dataloader = train_dataloader,\n",
        "                                                loss_fn = loss_fn,\n",
        "                                                optimizer = optimizer)\n",
        "\n",
        "        test_loss, test_accuracy = test_step(model = model,\n",
        "                                             dataloader = test_dataloader,\n",
        "                                             loss_fn = loss_fn)\n",
        "\n",
        "        if test_loss < best_test_loss:\n",
        "            best_test_loss = test_loss\n",
        "            file_name = \"best_model.pt\"\n",
        "\n",
        "            save_checkpoint(file_name, model, epoch, best_test_loss, optimizer, test_accuracy)\n",
        "\n",
        "        print(f\"Epoch: {epoch + 1} | \",\n",
        "              f\"Train Loss: {train_loss:.4f} | \",\n",
        "              f\"Train Accuracy: {train_accuracy:.4f} | \",\n",
        "              f\"Test Loss: {test_loss:.4f} | \",\n",
        "              f\"Test Accuracy: {test_accuracy:.4f}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        results[\"train_loss\"].append(train_loss)\n",
        "        results[\"train_accuracy\"].append(train_accuracy)\n",
        "        results[\"test_loss\"].append(test_loss)\n",
        "        results[\"test_accuracy\"].append(test_accuracy)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return results"
      ]
    },

        "\n",
        "EPOCHS = 100\n",
        "\n",
        "MODEL_RESULTS = train(model = model.to(device),\n",
        "                      train_dataloader = train_dataloader,\n",
        "                      test_dataloader = test_dataloader,\n",
        "                      loss_fn = loss_fn,\n",
        "                      optimizer = optimizer,\n",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "6bpYRHkEKo7D"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "#Function to plot the loss and metrics during each training epoch\n",
        "def plot_loss_metric_curve(model_results:Dict[str,List[float]]):\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_loss = model_results[\"train_loss\"]\n",
        "    test_loss = model_results[\"test_loss\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    train_accuracy = [float(value) for value in model_results[\"train_accuracy\"]]\n",
        "    test_accuracy = [float(value) for value in model_results[\"test_accuracy\"]]\n",
        "\n",
        "    fig,axes = plt.subplots(nrows = 1, ncols = 2, figsize = (10,4))\n",
        "    plt.style.use(\"ggplot\")\n",
        "    axes = axes.flat\n",
        "\n",
        "    axes[0].plot(train_loss, color = \"red\", label = \"Train\")\n",
        "    axes[0].plot(test_loss, color = \"blue\", label = \"Test\")\n",
        "    axes[0].set_title(\"CrossEntropyLoss\", fontsize = 12, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[0].set_xlabel(\"Epochs\", fontsize = 10, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[0].set_ylabel(\"Loss\", fontsize = 10, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[0].legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "    axes[1].plot(train_accuracy, color = \"red\", label = \"Train\")\n",
        "    axes[1].plot(test_accuracy, color = \"blue\", label = \"Test\")\n",
        "    axes[1].set_title(\"Metric of performance: Accuracy\", fontsize = 12, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[1].set_xlabel(\"Epochs\", fontsize = 10, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[1].set_ylabel(\"Score\", fontsize = 10, fontweight = \"bold\", color = \"black\")\n",
        "    axes[1].legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "    fig.tight_layout()\n",
        "    fig.show()"
      ]
    },
    {

      "source": [
        "model.to(device)\n",
        "model.load_state_dict(checkpoint[\"model\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "y_pred_train = []\n",
        "y_train = []\n",
        "y_pred_test = []\n",
        "y_test = []\n",
        "\n",
        "model.eval()\n",
        "with torch.inference_mode():\n",
        "\n",
        "    for batch,(X_train_batch,y_train_batch) in tqdm(enumerate(train_dataloader)):\n",
        "        X_train_batch,y_train_batch = X_train_batch.to(device), y_train_batch\n",
        "        y_pred_logits_train = model(X_train_batch)\n",
        "        y_pred_probs_train = torch.softmax(y_pred_logits_train.cpu(), dim = 1)\n",
        "        y_pred_class_train = torch.argmax(y_pred_probs_train, dim = 1)\n",
        "        y_pred_train.append(y_pred_class_train)\n",
        "        y_train.append(y_train_batch)\n",
        "\n",
        "    for batch,(X_test_batch,y_test_batch) in tqdm(enumerate(test_dataloader)):\n",
        "        X_test_batch,y_test_batch = X_test_batch.to(device), y_test_batch\n",
        "        y_pred_logits_test = model(X_test_batch)\n",
        "        y_pred_probs_test = torch.softmax(y_pred_logits_test.cpu(), dim = 1)\n",
        "        y_pred_class_test = torch.argmax(y_pred_probs_test, dim = 1)\n",
        "        y_pred_test.append(y_pred_class_test)\n",
        "        y_test.append(y_test_batch)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vGrZuP5XLGNO"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "y_pred_test = torch.cat(y_pred_test).numpy()\n",
        "y_pred_train = torch.cat(y_pred_train).numpy()\n",
        "\n",
        "y_train = torch.cat(y_train).numpy()\n",
        "y_test = torch.cat(y_test).numpy()"
      ]
    },
